Sep 11 2007 	Excellent Location No Maintainence	The owners of this hotel probably realise that they have an excellent location. They know that the property is not too large to fill and given the locational advantage (Baker Street tube station is 5min walking distance) they will always get idiots like me who will pay GBP 100 + for a lousy room.Would still consider this as you do not get too many better options for this price in Central London. But if you do, pls stay away. The hotel staff is not arrogant but has a &quot;you need me, I don't need you&quot; kind of attitude.Expect a basic room with barely clean toilets. No elevators, cramped corridor. Wodden structure and Road facing so noise levels can be disturbing. If the idea is to explore London from a central location and use the hotel to just come back late at night and crash then book. Else please use the review and stay away !	
