Oct 4 2004	A Birdlover's Idyll	Love this hotel -- it feels like my second home. I always stay at the Regents Park on my way back to America from overseas. The lobby has a feathered resident, Zilli the African Grey Parrot, who likes to chew up, oh, passports, credit cards, what have you...! The staff are quiet and friendly; they'll fix you up with a ride to the airport, or recommend a favorite London museum (try the Imperial War Museum). Rooms are small but complete. Get a room facing the back (Gloucester Place road noise). Good water pressure, good hot water. Food at adjoining Singapura restaurant is tasty; conti breakfast nice and filling. A quick walk to the Queen Mum's rose garden in Regent's Park. But the best part... is Zilli the bird!	
