Aug 4 2004	Very Nice Place to Stay	Stayed in this hotel July 17-20th 2004 and booked it due to the previous reviews on this site. This hotel is well situated and is very comfortable and clean. The standard of service and room quality is much lower in London then elsewhere, but I felt that this property gave me value for my money. The only complaint I have was that it was hot during my stay, and unfortunately in order to get air into the room, we had to have the window open. As we were in the front of the hotel, we overlooked the street which is a very busy street with buses and cars running up it all night long. This would not bother me in the fall or winter, but if you stay in the summer I would suggest you ask for a back facing room. The breakfast was good, with a reasonable assortment of options, but the 10 cereals (only 3) and the pain au chocolate the other reviewer mention were not present during our stay, however it was varied enough for the 4 days we were there. Note for the English Breakfast you have to pay extra. I found the beds a little hard for my liking, but to each their own. The location is fantastic otherwise, very close to Baker Street Tube Station with lots of shops and restaurants all around. I would definately stay there again.	
