Mar 12 2004	A real find	This hotel is close to the centre of London and also to one of the city's loveliest green spaces, Regent's Park. The rooms and studios are simply but comfortably furnished, and clean. Someone with a green thumb makes sure that plants flourish in all the public areas, even outside the entrance in February, and Zili -- a delightful parrot -- takes an intelligent interest in all the guests. Mohammed Asas, the manager, who presides over the reception desk by day, could easily double as a concierge at the Ritz. He is gracious and kind and gives excellent advice on every kind of practical problem; his shrewd shopping recommendations would do Which? (or Consumer Reports in the US) proud. For an alternative to the very good Malaysian and Chinese food in the downstairs restaurant, I suggest La Gauloise -- a 5-minute walk around the corner, on Melcombe Street -- where the miraculously light and airy quiches and first-rate salads would not be out of place in Paris, and are reasonably priced.	
Oct 4 2003	Wonderful stay	My husband and I stayed at the Regents Park and were thrilled. We found it easily accessable to everything you could possibly want to see in London via Baker street station and the &quot;Tube&quot;, which connected easily to the overground trian, or the double decker buses. We happened to be there during the summer heat wave of the century and in a country that does not do air conditioning this could have been a problem. Howerever I found this charming hotel above average for the area and price. We had a room facing the courtyard and it was quiet and cool. The water pressure in the shower was good and though the room was small, typical for London, it accomodated us very nicely. The Regents Park restaurant is absolutely the best chinese food I have ever experienced. This is for real. It is a little pricey but believe me it is worth it. We were there for two weeks and we ate there every night except three. We never got tired of it. It was so good. I would recommend the restaurant if you are in London no matter where you decide to stay.	
